# Kairos Education (Netlify static)

## 배포

- Publish directory: `public` ([netlify.toml](../netlify.toml)). No build step.
- **Manual deploy only** — local edits do not update production until the user uploads to Netlify. Do not say "push to deploy" unless Git is connected.
- Live URL and domain: read [PROJECT.md](../PROJECT.md) (user must fill in `YOUR-SITE.netlify.app`).

## Pages

- Root: `public/index.html` (language picker)
- Locales: `public/en/`, `ko/`, `zh/`, `th/` — each is a single large `index.html` with inline CSS
- **English (`en`) is the content source of truth** — most detailed (~1060 lines); other locales are shorter (~540 lines)

## Netlify Forms (one per locale)

| `name` | path |
|--------|------|
| `contact` | `/en/` |
| `contact-kr` | `/ko/` |
| `contact-zh` | `/zh/` |
| `contact-th` | `/th/` |

Forms use `data-netlify="true"`, hidden `form-name`, and honeypot. After form markup changes, user must redeploy. Form tests only on deployed URL.

## When editing

1. Ask or infer **which language(s)** — default to only what the user requested.
2. Contact info is duplicated: `Ronkim2015@gmail.com`, Kakao `http://pf.kakao.com/_uWJKX`
3. Keep stack **plain HTML/CSS** unless the user asks for a framework.
4. Remind user to **redeploy** and where to check `PROJECT.md` for live URL.

## Task scope (if user omits)

- Content baseline: English page
- Deploy: user (manual Netlify upload)
